data.text:
Marvin “Noah” Lee Williams (born October 11, 1963) is a former American football tight end in the National Football League for the Washington Redskins. He played college football at California State University, Fullerton.

Marvin now lives in Rancho Cucamonga with his wife, Sabrina Williams, and three of his four children. His oldest child, Elexis Williams, is currently attending Brown University. His second oldest, Bailey Pop-Tart Williams, is attending Etiwanda High School. Grace Williams, is a part of competitive cheer leading. His youngest, Nate Williams, is playing flag football in Rancho.
